Q11 . If objects are overlapping, how to improve RCNN?
If many objects are on top of each other, itâ€™s hard to detect them correctly.
Problem:
RCNN might draw one big box for all or miss some objects.

ğŸ› ï¸ How to improve RCNN for overlapping objects:
Use more region proposals â¤ Generate more candidate regions so nothing gets missed.
Use better anchor boxes (in Faster RCNN) â¤ Use different shapes and sizes of boxes to match objects better.
Train on more overlapping examples â¤ Add images with overlapping objects to your training data.
Use Soft-NMS (Soft Non-Max Suppression) â¤ Instead of removing overlapping boxes, reduce their scores â€” helps keep valid detections.

